			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			I remember there used to be a waiting period in between attacks? May I ask what is so wrong with that? I personally feel that at max one successful attack a turn be allowed per person on another person. To make it clearer, let's say A broke through B's defences. He has to wait another turn before attacking B but can still attack others.<br />
<br />
It prevents raping which isn't at all helpful unless you're already superior to the one whose planets you're raping which is just a form of bullying the weak. It may be part of the game, bullying the weak, but it seems to become dominant in the game above all other types of combat.<br />
<br />
The worst thing about being raped now is that one has no chance to do anything unless he is online like 24 hours and notices the first attack and hence is able to take action against the attacker. If not, once your defenses are broken, you're pretty much screwed.<br />
<br />
And people pretty much rape each other of planets in a normal war, leaving both with underdeveloped planets which frankly IMO is quite dumb.<br />
<br />
But I want to know why people are so against a restriction on the attacks one can make?						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
				</TR>
	
		
