			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Near the end of the last set, I was dying on a daily basis.<br />
<br />
However, I'm against limiting successful attacks for one simple reason. . .<br />
<br />
Real life.<br />
<br />
if you were to limit the frequency of attacks, it would push the game farther away into the fiction half of Science Fiction. After all, the only limit one country has (today) on how often they can attack another is a resource limit.<br />
<br />
However, I'd say one possible alternative to a time limit is to make any subsequent attacks (after the first successful one) lower your personal honor.<br />
<br />
Then, make honor connected to other things like the PP gained from commerce and maybe even the productivity/waste rate of recently sieged planets.<br />
<br />
Anyway, just my 2 PP.			   <P align=right></P>
